The `list` command should be able to output in CSV format for easier parsing, because the default output format is designed to be human readable.

For example:

    % deft list --csv
    new,1,shiny-buttons
    new,2,irritating-noises
    in-progress,1,gradient-fills
    in-progress,2,rounded-corner

It should be possible to select the CSV dialect as an optional parameter to the --csv option. For example:

    % deft list --csv excel
    ...

The default format should probably be excel.
